<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 3:18PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Roosevelt, southeastern Valley, northeastern McCone and northwestern
Richland Counties through 415 PM MDT...
At 317 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles south of Wolf Point, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Wolf Point, Poplar and Vida.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
